{
  "texts": [
    "The Fully Connected NETwork (FCNET) was tested using a Leave One Out cross-validation scheme in 6 metrics (MSE: Mean Squared Error; MAE: Mean Absolute Error; PCC: Pearson Correlation Coefficient; CS: Cosine Similarity; KL Kullback-Leiber and JS: Jensen-Shannon Divergences).",
    "In addition, we tested against two benchmark models: Huber and Null regressors.",
    "FCNET showed a significant improvement in all metrics evaluated.",
    "Both Huber and Null models were also tested in the same framework, that is, the predicted likelihoods weighted by the same anatomical prior (see Methods).",
    "Bold numbers indicate better performance; lower is better for MSE, MAE, KL, and JS while higher is better for CS and PCC."
  ]
}